    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "41e7c634_71f0f218",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/internal/model/query.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 32,
      "author": {
        "id": 1398165
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-23T03:44:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I also considered a while and then decided to create an intermediate SearchQuery obj as in Py.\n\nThe search flow contains 3 major steps :\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \n                                           |— query on TagIndex; get builds on Builds via ids  \npreprocessing -\u003e determine which subflow --|\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \n                                           |— normal query directly on Builds kind\n\nNewSearchQuery is in the preprocessing.\n\n1. We need this intermediate obj as two subflows use different datatore.Query but need some\nsame info which can be preprocessed and converted at the same place before, e.g. timeRange, idRange, tags from pb to str slices and so on.\n\n2. Another potential benefit could be the low coupling and better isolation if case of SearchBuildsRequest or repo structure get changed. An intermediate usually benefits for the 3-layer repo and is used between the handler layer to the controller/business layer.\nOur repo seems like only two layers - handler(which handle RPC and do business logic) and Repository layer. But it doesn\u0027t hurt to have it.",
      "parentUuid": "b4fd425d_ec5f6fc0",
      "revId": "7126a295a6f29ac0673bfc4bcc82e17e8650c29b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
